3 Sec. 2. K.S.A. 8-1568 is hereby amended to read as follows: 8-1568.
4 (a) (1) (A) Any driver of a motor vehicle who knowingly fails or refuses to
5 bring such driver's vehicle to a stop for a pursuing police vehicle or police
6 bicycle, when given visual or audible signal to bring the vehicle to a stop,
7 shall be guilty as provided by subsection (c)(1).
8 (B) Any driver of a motor vehicle who knowingly otherwise flees or
9 attempts to elude a pursuing police vehicle or police bicycle, when given
10 visual or audible signal to bring the vehicle to a stop, shall be guilty as
11 provided by subsection (c)(1).
12 (2) It shall be an affirmative defense to any prosecution under
13 subsection (a)(1) that the driver's conduct in violation of such subsection
14 was caused by such driver's reasonable belief that the vehicle or bicycle
15 pursuing such driver's vehicle is not a police vehicle or police bicycle.
16 (b) Any driver of a motor vehicle who knowingly fails or refuses to
17 bring such driver's vehicle to a stop, or who otherwise flees or attempts to
18 elude a pursuing police vehicle or police bicycle, when given visual or
19 audible signal to bring the vehicle to a stop, and who:
20 (1) Commits any of the following during a police pursuit, shall be
21 guilty as provided by subsection (c)(2):
22 (A) Fails to stop for a police road block;
23 (B) drives around tire deflating devices placed by a police officer;
24 (C) engages in reckless driving as defined by K.S.A. 8-1566, and
25 amendments thereto;
26 (D) is involved in any motor vehicle accident or intentionally causes
27 damage to property;
28 (E) commits five or more moving violations; or
29 (F) is operating a stolen motor vehicle;
30 (2) is attempting to elude capture for the commission of any felony,
31 shall be guilty as provided by subsection (c)(2);
32 (3) is attempting to elude capture for the commission of engaging in
33 a street stunt in violation of section 1, and amendments thereto, shall be
34 guilty as provided by subsection (c)(3); or
35 (3)(4) knowingly drives the wrong way into an opposing lane of
36 travel on a divided highway as defined in K.S.A. 8-1414, and amendments
37 thereto, knowingly departs the appropriate lane of travel into an opposing
38 lane of travel on any roadway causing an evasive maneuver by another
39 driver, knowingly drives through any intersection causing an evasive
40 maneuver by another driver or causes a collision involving another driver,
41 shall be guilty as provided by subsection (c)(3).
42 (c) (1) Violation of subsection (a) is a:
43 (A) Class B nonperson misdemeanor when the person being

