1 sentenced has no prior convictions for a violation of subsection (a) or (b);
2 (B) class A nonperson misdemeanor when the person being sentenced
3 has one prior conviction for a violation of subsection (a) or (b); or
4 (C) severity level 9, person felony when the person being sentenced
5 has two or more prior convictions for a violation of subsection (a) or (b).
6 (2) Violation of subsection (b)(1) or (b)(2) is a severity level 9,
7 person felony.
8 (3) Violation of subsection (b)(3) or (b)(4) is a severity level 7,
9 person felony.
10 (4) In addition to the penalty described in paragraph (2), the court
11 shall impose a fine of not less than $500 when the driver is operating a
12 stolen motor vehicle during the commission of the offense.
13 (d) The signal given by the police officer may be by hand, voice,
14 emergency light or siren:
15 (1) If the officer giving such signal is within or upon an official police
16 vehicle or police bicycle at the time the signal is given, the vehicle or
17 bicycle shall be appropriately marked showing it to be an official police
18 vehicle or police bicycle; or
19 (2) if the officer giving such signal is not utilizing an official police
20 vehicle or police bicycle at the time the signal is given, the officer shall be
21 in uniform, prominently displaying such officer's badge of office at the
22 time the signal is given.
23 (e) For the purpose of this section:
24 (1) "Conviction" means a final conviction without regard to whether
25 sentence was suspended or probation granted after such conviction.
26 Forfeiture of bail, bond or collateral deposited to secure a defendant's
27 appearance in court, which forfeiture has not been vacated, shall be
28 equivalent to a conviction. For the purpose of determining whether a
29 conviction is a first, second, third or subsequent conviction in sentencing
30 under this section, it is irrelevant whether an offense occurred before or
31 after conviction for a previous offense.
32 (2) "Appropriately marked" official police vehicle or police bicycle
33 shall include, but not be limited to, any police vehicle or bicycle equipped
34 with functional emergency lights or siren or both and which the emergency
35 lights or siren or both have been activated for the purpose of signaling a
36 driver to stop a motor vehicle.
37 (f) The division of vehicles of the department of revenue shall
38 promote public awareness of the provisions of this section when persons
39 apply for or renew such person's driver's license.
40 Sec. 3. K.S.A. 8-1568 is hereby repealed.
41 Sec. 4. This act shall take effect and be in force from and after its
42 publication in the statute book.

